{"total_count": 19, "incomplete_results": false, "items": [{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/44", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/44/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/44/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/44/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/matze/pkgconfig/issues/44", "id": 430038788, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU0MzAwMzg3ODg=", "number": 44, "title": "missing setup.py in source file from github", "user": {"login": "dirteat", "id": 13554957, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNTU0OTU3", "avatar_url": "https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/13554957?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/dirteat", "html_url": "https://github.com/dirteat", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dirteat/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dirteat/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dirteat/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dirteat/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dirteat/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dirteat/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dirteat/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dirteat/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dirteat/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2019-04-06T14:23:14Z", "updated_at": "2019-12-14T09:34:22Z", "closed_at": "2019-04-07T10:12:36Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Hi there,\r\nthe pkgconfig-1.5.1.tar.gz file from github is missing setup.py, whereas the one from pypi is fine. That's quite confusing to have 2 source files with the same name but not same content, especially when one is not compiling :-/\r\n\r\nCheers,\r\nChris.", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/43", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/43/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/43/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/43/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/matze/pkgconfig/issues/43", "id": 427345957, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU0MjczNDU5NTc=", "number": 43, "title": "1.5.0 is forcing upgrade of pytest due to xmlsec", "user": {"login": "dcramer", "id": 23610, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIzNjEw", "avatar_url": "https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/23610?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/dcramer", "html_url": "https://github.com/dcramer", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dcramer/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dcramer/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dcramer/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dcramer/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dcramer/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dcramer/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dcramer/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dcramer/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dcramer/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 11, "created_at": "2019-03-31T01:20:04Z", "updated_at": "2019-04-02T07:47:16Z", "closed_at": "2019-04-01T19:30:02Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I'm not sure how you're building the distribution, but when you install xmlsec, which relies on an unbounded pkgconfig, it's causing pytest to upgrade in our environments. This seems unintentional (I reviewed the pyproject.toml), but I'm not sure what the fix is.\r\n\r\nI'm still in the process of debugging but the easy repro is just ``pip install -U pkgconfig`` and you'll see it trying to install pytest.", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/42", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/42/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/42/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/42/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/matze/pkgconfig/issues/42", "id": 420589889, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU0MjA1ODk4ODk=", "number": 42, "title": "_query should check exit code of pkg-info", "user": {"login": "ThomasWaldmann", "id": 356103, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM1NjEwMw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/356103?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann", "html_url": "https://github.com/ThomasWaldmann", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 6, "created_at": "2019-03-13T16:13:47Z", "updated_at": "2019-11-04T10:22:36Z", "closed_at": "2019-03-14T07:55:22Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "pkginfo 1.4.0\r\n```\r\n>>> from pkgconfig import parse\r\n>>> parse('openssl')  # existing lib\r\ndefaultdict(<class 'list'>, {'libraries': ['ssl', 'crypto'], ...})\r\n>>> parse('libxxxxxxxxxx')  # non-existing lib!\r\ndefaultdict(<class 'list'>, {...})\r\n```\r\n\r\nfor a non-existing lib (see last example), guess there could be some exception, but it fails silently.\r\n\r\ni had a quick look and the main problem might be that `_query` does not check the exit code of `pkg-info`, which is 1 in the error case and 0 in case it is successful.\r\n\r\nguess it should raise a relatively generic exception in the error case, so it does not fail silently.\r\n\r\nadditionally to that, maybe the calls that rely on a lib being actually there could first check if the lib is installed and if not raise a more specific exception \"lib not found\".", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/40", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/40/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/40/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/40/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/matze/pkgconfig/issues/40", "id": 420267822, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU0MjAyNjc4MjI=", "number": 40, "title": ".parse() result has empty-list (real) members", "user": {"login": "ThomasWaldmann", "id": 356103, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM1NjEwMw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/356103?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann", "html_url": "https://github.com/ThomasWaldmann", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 6, "created_at": "2019-03-13T00:47:32Z", "updated_at": "2019-03-14T11:36:19Z", "closed_at": "2019-03-14T07:54:04Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "pkginfo 1.4.0\r\n```\r\n>>> from pkgconfig import parse\r\n>>> parse('openssl')\r\ndefaultdict(<class 'list'>, {'libraries': ['ssl', 'crypto'], 'define_macros': []})\r\n>>> parse('liblz4')\r\ndefaultdict(<class 'list'>, {'libraries': ['lz4'], 'define_macros': []})\r\n>>> parse('libzstd')\r\ndefaultdict(<class 'list'>, {'libraries': ['zstd'], 'define_macros': []})\r\n>>> parse('libxxxxxxxxxx')\r\ndefaultdict(<class 'list'>, {'define_macros': []})\r\n```\r\n\r\nNotable:\r\n- define_macros always there, even if empty (other empty stuff not there and as it is a list-defaultdict, it does not need to be there when empty)\r\n- for a non-existing lib (see last example), guess there could be some exception, but it fails silently.", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/34", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/34/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/34/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/34/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/matze/pkgconfig/issues/34", "id": 398115276, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUzOTgxMTUyNzY=", "number": 34, "title": "use setuptools_scm?", "user": {"login": "ThomasWaldmann", "id": 356103, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM1NjEwMw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/356103?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann", "html_url": "https://github.com/ThomasWaldmann", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2019-01-11T03:19:55Z", "updated_at": "2019-03-14T08:22:07Z", "closed_at": "2019-03-14T08:22:06Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "it helps with versioning (via git tags) and also keeping the manifest up-to-date (uses files committed to git, unless you tell otherwise).\r\n\r\nnote: currently `MANIFEST.in` refers to `test.py` which does not exist.\r\n\r\ni use it in some projects and i'm quite happy with it.", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/32", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/32/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/32/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/32/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/matze/pkgconfig/issues/32", "id": 398107364, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUzOTgxMDczNjQ=", "number": 32, "title": "openssl version parsing error", "user": {"login": "ThomasWaldmann", "id": 356103, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM1NjEwMw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/356103?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann", "html_url": "https://github.com/ThomasWaldmann", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ThomasWaldmann/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2019-01-11T02:43:53Z", "updated_at": "2019-03-13T16:01:09Z", "closed_at": "2019-03-13T16:01:09Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "pkgconfig crashes while checking the openssl version number:\r\n```\r\n>>> pkgconfig.installed('openssl', '>= 1.1.0')\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"/home/user/w/borg-env/lib/python3.5/site-packages/pkgconfig/pkgconfig.py\", line 161, in installed\r\n    result = _compare_versions(modversion, number)\r\n  File \"/home/user/w/borg-env/lib/python3.5/site-packages/pkgconfig/pkgconfig.py\", line 44, in _compare_versions\r\n    n1 = normalize(v1)\r\n  File \"/home/user/w/borg-env/lib/python3.5/site-packages/pkgconfig/pkgconfig.py\", line 42, in normalize\r\n    return [int(x) for x in re.sub(r'(\\.0+)*$', '', v).split(\".\")]\r\n  File \"/home/user/w/borg-env/lib/python3.5/site-packages/pkgconfig/pkgconfig.py\", line 42, in <listcomp>\r\n    return [int(x) for x in re.sub(r'(\\.0+)*$', '', v).split(\".\")]\r\nValueError: invalid literal for int() with base 10: '0j'\r\n\r\nDuring handling of the above exception, another exception occurred:\r\n\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"<stdin>\", line 1, in <module>\r\n  File \"/home/user/w/borg-env/lib/python3.5/site-packages/pkgconfig/pkgconfig.py\", line 164, in installed\r\n    raise ValueError(msg)\r\nValueError: >= 1.1.0 is not a correct version specifier\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt's on Debian 9:\r\n```\r\nii  openssl                              1.1.0j-1~deb9u1                   amd64        Secure Sockets Layer toolkit - cryptographic utility\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote: openssl 1.1 is incompatible to 1.0, so while the check for a specific update release (like `j`) is maybe not that important (except for security fixes, early bug fixes), the check for 1.1 vs. 1.0 is fundamentally important.", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/31", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/31/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/31/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/31/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/matze/pkgconfig/issues/31", "id": 391085429, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUzOTEwODU0Mjk=", "number": 31, "title": "Please expose --modversion", "user": {"login": "hughmcmaster", "id": 11186136, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjExMTg2MTM2", "avatar_url": "https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/11186136?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/hughmcmaster", "html_url": "https://github.com/hughmcmaster", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hughmcmaster/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hughmcmaster/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hughmcmaster/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hughmcmaster/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hughmcmaster/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hughmcmaster/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hughmcmaster/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hughmcmaster/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hughmcmaster/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2018-12-14T12:06:47Z", "updated_at": "2018-12-15T11:18:27Z", "closed_at": "2018-12-14T18:47:12Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "`pkg-config --modversion <package>` oututs the version information of a package's libraries.\r\n\r\nFor example, `pkg-config --modversion icu-i18n` outputs 63.1 (assuming that version is installed).\r\n\r\nIt would be very useful to be able to get this information using your pkgconfig module.\r\n\r\nThe syntax would be `pkgconfig.modversion('package')` or similar.\r\n\r\nIf you don't have time, I can look at preparing a pull request for this.\r\n\r\nThank you", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/30", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/30/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/30/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/30/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/matze/pkgconfig/issues/30", "id": 386667001, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUzODY2NjcwMDE=", "number": 30, "title": "win32 (msys2) \"\\r\" in keys for .variables()", "user": {"login": "briend", "id": 6015639, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjYwMTU2Mzk=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/6015639?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/briend", "html_url": "https://github.com/briend", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/briend/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/briend/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/briend/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/briend/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/briend/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/briend/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/briend/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/briend/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/briend/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [{"id": 51216848, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw1MTIxNjg0OA==", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/labels/bug", "name": "bug", "color": "fc2929", "default": true, "description": null}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2018-12-03T05:41:30Z", "updated_at": "2018-12-04T09:16:33Z", "closed_at": "2018-12-04T09:16:33Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Hi!  Thanks for the library!  I'm hoping it will help me dynamically get a configuration variable for a package in a dynamic way from python.  I'm trying to support several platforms, and I'm having a problem specific to windows and the \\r\\n line feeds.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/matze/pkgconfig/blob/master/pkgconfig/pkgconfig.py#L132\r\n\r\nOn MSYS2 (windows \"unix\" environment) this can be pretty ugly, leaving the keys with the string \"\\r\" at the end of some keys (but not all keys):\r\n\r\n>>> pkgconfig.variables('zlib')\r\n{u'sharedlibdir': u'C:/msys64/mingw64/bin', u'exec_prefix\\r': u'C:/msys64/mingw64', u'pcfiledir\\r': u'C:\\\\msys64\\\\mingw64\\\\lib\\\\pkgconfig', u'includedir\\r': u'C:/msys64/mingw64/include', u'libdir\\r': u'C:/msys64/mingw64/lib', u'prefix\\r': u'C:/msys64/mingw64'}\r\n", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/27", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/27/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/27/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/27/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/matze/pkgconfig/issues/27", "id": 365247782, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUzNjUyNDc3ODI=", "number": 27, "title": "Switch from nose to pytest", "user": {"login": "ericvw", "id": 1284017, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEyODQwMTc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/1284017?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ericvw", "html_url": "https://github.com/ericvw", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ericvw/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ericvw/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ericvw/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ericvw/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ericvw/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ericvw/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ericvw/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ericvw/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ericvw/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2018-09-30T18:19:25Z", "updated_at": "2018-10-15T06:56:30Z", "closed_at": "2018-10-15T06:56:30Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "[`nose`](https://nose.readthedocs.io/en/latest/) has been in maintenance mode over the past several years and is not actively developed (see Notes section at the top of the main page).\r\n\r\nGiven that [`pytest`](https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/) is also mentioned in the [`unittest`](https://docs.python.org/3/library/unittest.html) documentation as an alternative test runner/framework, @matze, would be open if I migrate the tests over to `pytest`-style and structure?", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/26", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/26/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/26/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/26/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/matze/pkgconfig/issues/26", "id": 352616855, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUzNTI2MTY4NTU=", "number": 26, "title": "Request for new release to PyPI (1.4.0)", "user": {"login": "ericvw", "id": 1284017, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEyODQwMTc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/1284017?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.co