onfig/issues/15/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/15/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/15/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/matze/pkgconfig/issues/15", "id": 192805420, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUxOTI4MDU0MjA=", "number": 15, "title": "testing issues on system defaulting to lib64", "user": {"login": "kiwifb", "id": 151475, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE1MTQ3NQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/151475?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb", "html_url": "https://github.com/kiwifb", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 8, "created_at": "2016-12-01T10:21:58Z", "updated_at": "2016-12-02T09:35:18Z", "closed_at": "2016-12-01T10:45:29Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I probably relied on travis when I did that last push. Although I would have thought the \"listify\" pull would be the one responsible, but I definitely tested that.\r\n```\r\n....F.\r\n======================================================================\r\nFAIL: test.test_parse\r\n----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"/usr/lib64/python2.7/site-packages/nose/case.py\", line 197, in runTest\r\n    self.test(*self.arg)\r\n  File \"/scratch2/portage/dev-python/pkgconfig-1.2.1/work/pkgconfig-1.2.1/test.py\", line 47, in test_parse\r\n    nt.assert_true('/usr/lib64' in config['library_dirs'] or not config['library_dirs'])\r\nAssertionError: False is not true\r\n```\r\nbecause `/usr/lib64` is the default path for libraries it is omitted. on the other hand I have `/usr/lib` in `config['library_dirs']`. I think it would be better to put a non regular name in one of the fake `.pc` files (something like `/this_is_not_a real_library_path/do_not_use_me`) and test for it.\r\n\r\nI am overall confused by the logic of that particular assert statement.", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/14", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/14/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/14/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/14/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/matze/pkgconfig/issues/14", "id": 192780679, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUxOTI3ODA2Nzk=", "number": 14, "title": "tarball for 1.2.0 misses the data folder", "user": {"login": "kiwifb", "id": 151475, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE1MTQ3NQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/151475?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb", "html_url": "https://github.com/kiwifb", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2016-12-01T08:19:27Z", "updated_at": "2016-12-01T08:59:18Z", "closed_at": "2016-12-01T08:30:35Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Which is important if you want to run the testsuite. We packagers like to run testsuite before installing when we can. If you are not going to ship the data folder you shouldn't ship `test.py` either.", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/10", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/10/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/10/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/10/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/matze/pkgconfig/issues/10", "id": 189548811, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUxODk1NDg4MTE=", "number": 10, "title": "Use lists instead of sets", "user": {"login": "kiwifb", "id": 151475, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE1MTQ3NQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/151475?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb", "html_url": "https://github.com/kiwifb", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kiwifb/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2016-11-16T00:32:17Z", "updated_at": "2016-11-16T10:21:06Z", "closed_at": "2016-11-16T10:21:05Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nThe usage of sets has some potential drawback in wider use. I am guessing sets have been selected to avoid duplication in the output. Sets are very good for that. However sets have drawback:\r\n* order is not preserved. It is particularly annoying for `libraries` where is the order is often important depending on the linker\r\n* most distutils applications take lists as argument, not sets, which mean the output of `parse` has to be cast before being useful. I cannot think of an application requiring a set, feel free to show me one.\r\n\r\nBoth problems are solved by using list instead of set on the outset. list will preserve the order and be directly consumable by distutils. Duplication could be eliminated by applying a filter before returning the final list. However, such filter would have to go from the right rather than the left (i.e. keeping latest instance rather than the first). \r\n\r\nAfter discussion with my colleagues of `sagemath` we don't think the duplication in the output is a problem. It may be less elegant but `pkg-config` itself doesn't do anything about it - and it already filters output somewhat by default. Having worked on exotic platform I can unfortunately think of scenarios in which the duplication may be useful - especially if static libraries are involved. I'll admit reducing macros could be neat but the rest is a potential hazard.", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/9", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/9/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/9/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/9/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/matze/pkgconfig/issues/9", "id": 113218158, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUxMTMyMTgxNTg=", "number": 9, "title": "Distribute tests", "user": {"login": "FRidh", "id": 2129135, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIxMjkxMzU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/2129135?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/FRidh", "html_url": "https://github.com/FRidh", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/FRidh/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/FRidh/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/FRidh/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/FRidh/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/FRidh/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/FRidh/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/FRidh/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/FRidh/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/FRidh/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2015-10-25T10:29:08Z", "updated_at": "2015-10-27T11:16:50Z", "closed_at": "2015-10-26T07:14:50Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I was just packaging pkgconfig for Nix and to my surprise tests were not discovered. Apparently, `test.py` is not added to your manifest and thus the package on PyPi does not have the test suite. I recommend adding the tests since these are important for packagers as well.\n", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/8", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/8/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/8/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/matze/pkgconfig/issues/8/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/matze/pkgconfig/issues/8", "id": 99288172, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU5OTI4ODE3Mg==", "number": 8, "title": "Ability to get list of all packages defined in pkgconfig?", "user": {"login": "tanimislam", "id": 747905, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjc0NzkwNQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/747905?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tanimislam", "html_url": "https://github.com/tanimislam", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tanimislam/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tanimislam/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tanimislam/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tanimislam/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tanimislam/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tanimislam/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tanimislam/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tanimislam/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tanimislam/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2015-08-05T20:07:03Z", "updated_at": "2015-08-10T06:59:10Z", "closed_at": "2015-08-10T06:58:45Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Hello, is ther